28 Juillet 2017



The Motley Fool owns shares of and recommends Apple, Baidu, and PayPal Holdings. (NASDAQ:PYPL) during the first quarter, Holdings Channel reports. Institutional investors and hedge funds own 81.55% of the company's stock.Additionally, volume at Venmo, a key unit for PayPal, has doubled in the past year, reaching $8 billion in payments and benefiting from deals to allow Venmo use at US merchants that accept PayPal, and keeping the social payment app competitive with the rival bank-powered Zelle service. Renaissance Investment Group LLC now owns 108,249 shares of the credit services provider's stock worth $4,657,000 after buying an additional 2,666 shares during the last quarter.Paypal Holdings (NASDAQ:PYPL) now has a trailing P/E of 50.25 while its forward P/E according to Thomson Reuters is 27.73. PayPal Holdings Inc had 91 analyst reports since July 23, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel.In related news, Director Gail J. Mcgovern sold 1,800 shares of the business's stock in a transaction that occurred on Thursday, June 8th. Philadelphia Trust Co. raised its position in PayPal Holdings by 0.6% in the fourth quarter. NC raised its position in PayPal Holdings by 5.5% in the first quarter. The stock's quarterly performance specifies a shift of 30.31%, and its last twelve month performance is stands at 54.21% while moved 38.85% for the past six months. The Firm has ATR of 1.24 that is explaining range of a day's trading is high-low; ATR expands it to yesterday's closing price. At the open, shares were trading at 58.9. The stock has a 50 day moving average price of $54.90 and a 200-day moving average price of $47.03.Paypal Holdings Inc (NASDAQ:PYPL) late Wednesday posted market-beating second quarter earnings results and offered a full-year forecast that exceeded analysts' numbers. The credit services provider reported $0.46 earnings per share for the quarter, topping the Zacks' consensus estimate of $0.43 by $0.03. PayPal Holdings had a return on equity of 10.78% and a net margin of 12.60%. During the same quarter in the prior year, the firm earned $0.36 EPS.In terms of guidance, the company expects to see EPS in the range of $0.42 to $0.44 and revenues between $3.14 billion and $3.19 billion. This repurchase authorization permits the credit services provider to repurchase up to 9.3% of its shares through open market purchases. 22,701,727 shares of the company's stock traded hands.
